race.comment: Day 1 comes to an end on the turf. Going to throw up BOTTAS (12) following a narrow win in the Pilgrim where he jumped the race favourite. Improved nicely from his debut there and while the draw is sticky, he looks open to further improvement now. Already ticked the distance box and he'll take beating. GSTAAD (14) steps up to the mile for the first time after going under in the Dewhurst last start as the race favourite. That form looks very strong for this event and he's shown adaptability throughout his early career. Needs to stretch to the mile now, but if he can run the trip he'll be hard to hold out. ARGOS (9) got the job done in the Summer Stakes at Woodbine last time out and turned in a strong rating in the process. Can sustain a strong effort in the closing stages and with a touch of luck, he'll be right there at the finish. HEY NAY NAY (13) has to be included following a good win here last start at G3 level. OUTFIELDER (3) won well last start but is some query up in trip now.
